ce:section.ce:para:
EIS measurements were recorded in 0.1 M KOH electrolyte to research the interfacial processes and the charge transfer kinetics of the as-prepared catalysts. The Nyquist plots and the corresponding equivalent circuit diagram of various catalysts are presented in Fig. 7
                     . The impedance plot of each catalyst shows almost similar profiles with a semicircle. And then, an appropriate equivalent circuit was employed to fit the impedance spectra, as described in the inset of Fig. 7. According to the fitting results, the R

                        ct
                      (charge transfer resistances) of the NPCN-900 (129

                            Ω

                     ) was much smaller than those of NPCN-1000 (186.5 
                        Ω
                     ), NPCN-800 (338

                            Ω

                     ), NC (335.8 
                        Ω
                     ) and PCFs (567.2

                            Ω

                     ). The smaller charge transfer resistance of NPCN-900 clearly suggests a higher conductivity and better charge transport capability. Such a low interfacial charge transfer resistance of NPCN-900 is mainly attributed to its unique 3D porous network architecture with multidimensional electron transport pathways, high degree of graphitization and the moderate heteroatom doping level introduces strong electron donors into graphite structure [47].
